dct_title_s: State of New Jersey Board of Commerce and Navigation Survey of Manasquan Inlet
dct_description_sm: This survey consists of three map sheets in blueprint. The map depicts the Manasquan Inlet at the mouth of the Manasquan River and the Atlantic Ocean and nearby Point Pleasant Beach. Each map includes a profile along the crest of bar as a smaller inset map at the bottom of each sheet, depicted as A-A-A-A, B-B-B-B, and C-C-C-C. Information about high/low water levels, horizontal and vertical scales is also included.
Source map supplied by New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection
